{Immediately undermining Black's central construction. Defending the d4 pawn
with} d3 {doesn't work as after} (5... Nc6 {also fails to keep the d-pawn
alive.} 6. cxd4 cxd4 7. Qa4 {Pinning the knight and winning the d-pawn.} d3 8.
Ned4 Bd7 9. Bxd3 {White is a clean pawn up.}) (5... dxc3 {And now the simplest
route towards a clear advantage is} 6. Nxc3 {intending to take over the center
