Ne5 {Defending the d3 pawn and hitting Black's pawn on c6.} Bd6 {is strongly
met by} 11. Qa4 {with a double-attack on the c6 pawn and the bishop on a6.
White is clearly better.}) 6. Nf4 {Black does not have a good way of defending
