act swiftly or else he'll simply end up a pawn down.} 9. c3 {Reinforcing the
d4 pawn.} Nc6 {And now the engines simply recommend capturing the c5 pawn with
the novelty} 10. dxc5 {The e4 pawn is also about to drop.} Qa5 11. Be3 {
Defending the c5 pawn.} Nxe5 12. Nxe4 {White is a pawn up and is thus clearly
for choice. Qc2, Be2 and O-O are natural follow-ups.}) 7. Bf4 e6 8. Qd2 {
Clearing the way for O-O-O.} c5 9. dxc5 O-O 10. O-O-O {h4-h5 is coming next
