the checkmating threat of Qxh7.}) 7. Qe2 {when Black can no longer play} f6 {
because of} 8. exd5 cxd5 9. Nxd5 {nets White a pawn, the point being that} Qxd5
10. Bc4 {wins on the spot.}) 6. Nxe4 Nd7 {Preparing ...Nf6. White should
simply continue development with} (6... Nf6 {White should now double Black's
pawns with} 7. Nxf6+ {The natural recapture} Bxf6 {is not so good as White can
