on the f7 pawn.} f6 16. Ne4 Qd4 17. Re1 {Bxd5 followed by Nd6+/Nxf6+ is now a
big threat. Black is in big trouble.}) 9. Qg3 g6 {And now Leela likes} 10. a4 {
gaining space on the queenside.} Bg7 11. d4 Qxg3 12. hxg3 Bf5 13. c3 {
Reinforcing the d4 pawn.} O-O 14. a5 Nd7 15. O-O {White can continue with Bf4,
Re1 and the ROVER rook up and over Ra4-b4 with a slight advantage. Black is
pretty solid but lacks an active plan.} *

