d4 {runs into the strong intermediate move} 6. Bc4 $1 e6 7. Ne2 c5 8. Qg3 Nf6
9. d3 $16 {White castle short on the next turn and then play f2-f4 with a
clear advantage.}) 6. Be2 {A Caro-Pirc like setup with This is White's most
logical move, which was popularized by MVL. White is looking to castle first
