1. e4 {In this chapter, you will find several tactical combinations, all of
which arose from games in the Two-Knights variation. Some of these tactical
patterns have occurred in multiple games in this variation, i.e. they are
typical motifs. Note that a few of them are not easy so don't worry if you
don't find the correct solution on your first attempt. I'd recommend trying to
calculate the forcing variations until the end and not just trying to guess
the first move. Finally, I'd recommend setting the quiz timer to infinity or
at least a couple of minutes. It's 60 seconds by default because this is an
opening course and Chessable does not, as of the time I'm writing this, allow
for different quiz timers in different chapters. I hope you have some fun
trying to solve these puzzles!} *

