[FEN "r1bqk2r/p4ppp/2pbpn2/1p2N3/P7/3B4/1PPPQPPP/R1B1K2R b KQkq - 0 11"]
[PlyCount "6"]

11... Qc7 {Black has just defended the c6 pawn with his queen. Find White's
best move.} 12. Nxc6 {White picks up the c6 pawn. The knight is taboo since ...
Qxc6 is met by Bxb5, pinning and winning the queen.} b4 13. Nd4 a6 {In the
game 0-1 Aloma Vidal, Roberto (2443)-Moskalenko, Alexander 2020, White played
14.b3. Stronger was} 14. Nf5 {exploiting the pin along the e-file, which would
have given White a slight advantage.} *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Thematic Tactics"]
[Black "Exercise 6"]
