[PlyCount "10"]

7... Bf5 {GM Emilio Cordova has just played the natural ...Bf5. However, this
is a big blunder. What did Black miss?} 8. Bc4 {Attacking the queen, which
needs to hold on to the bishop on f5.} Qe4+ 9. Qxe4 Bxe4 10. Bxf7+ {This is
the point. White picks up the f7 pawn. This is a very common tactic in the
Two-Knights variation.} Kxf7 11. Ng5+ Kg6 12. Nxe4 {White was a clean pawn up
and easily converted his advantage in 1-0 (45) Yoo, C (2449)-Cordova, E (2570)
Saint Louis 2019.} *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Thematic Tactics"]
[Black "Exercise 7"]
[Result "*"]
[SetUp "1"]
[FEN "2kr1bnr/pp1n2pp/2p1pp2/q7/4NB2/1Q5P/P1P1BPP1/3R1RK1 b - - 0 14"]
[PlyCount "10"]

14... e5 {Super-GM Shakhriyar Mamedyarov with the Black pieces has just played
...e6-e5 to attack White's bishop on e5. What did he miss?} 15. Bg4 {White
ignores Black's move and instead counterattacks the knight on d7.} exf4 16.
Rxd7 ({The more forcing} 16. Bxd7+ Rxd7 17. Rxd7 Kxd7 18. Qxb7+ {also wins.})
16... Rxd7 17. Rd1 {Pilling on the pinned piece.} (17. Bxd7+ Kxd7 $2 18. Qxb7+
$18 {is also winning.}) 17... f5 18. Qe6 Qd8 19. Bxf5 {The rook on d7 is about
to drop and White quickly won in 1-0 Sadhwani, Raunak (2522)-Mamedyarov,
Shakhriyar (2770) PRO League 2020.} *

