[PlyCount "6"]

9... Bc5 {Black has just played ...Bc5. Is there anything wrong with this
seemingly normal developing move?} 10. Bxf7+ {Yes, this sacrifice once again
decides the game.} Kxf7 11. Qh5+ {This is the point. White recoups the bishop
with this fork.} g6 12. Qxc5 {White was a clean pawn up and easily brought the
point home in 1-0 Luch, Michal (2433)-Borbjerggaard, Lars (2339) Denmark 2012.}
*

