[SetUp "1"]
[FEN "r2qkbnr/pp1npppp/6b1/1B1pN3/6P1/2N4P/PPPP1P2/R1BQK2R b KQkq - 0 8"]
[PlyCount "8"]

8... Ngf6 {Black has just played ...Ngf6, defending the pawn on d5 and the
knight on d7. How did White proceed?} 9. Nxd5 {White picked up the d5 pawn,
exploiting the fact that the knight on f6 is overworked as it needs to defend
his colleague on d7.} Qa5 10. b4 {Another nice tactic!} Qxb5 11. Nc7+ Kd8 12.
Nxb5 *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Thematic Tactics"]
[Black "Exercise 13"]
[Result "*"]
[SetUp "1"]
[FEN "r1bqkb1r/pp2pppp/2p2n2/8/2B5/5N2/PPPPQPPP/R1B1K2R b KQkq - 0 8"]
[PlyCount "8"]

8... Bg4 {Black has just played the natural developing move ...Bg4. What did
Black miss?} 9. Bxf7+ {Here we go again! Yet another instance of the Bxf7
sacrifice. This time, White picks up the bishop on g4.} ({Also winning is} 9.
Ne5 $1 {because} Bxe2 {allows} 10. Bxf7#) 9... Kxf7 10. Ne5+ Ke8 11. Nxg4 Nxg4
12. Qxg4 {White was a pawn up and had no trouble bringing the point home in
1-0 Priyanka, K. (2218)-Larina, Marija (1948) Titled Tuesday 2020.} *

